## §5 report protocol

### When to use §5 output

- Planning and specification when scope, schedule, and dependencies are baselined
- Verify and release when burn-down, risks, and stakeholder commitments face pressure
- Major scope or priority shifts that invalidate prior plans

### Phase awareness

- **Strongest:** B (Specify / planning emphasis) and E–F (Verify, Release) — **high**
- **Moderate:** C–D when execution variance threatens the plan — **medium**
- **Lighter:** A unless charter and constraints are undefined — **low–medium**

### What to inspect

- Scope management, change control, and definition of done across work items
- Schedule risk, critical path assumptions, and dependency exposure
- Resource allocation, capacity, and skill coverage vs. commitments
- Stakeholder communication plan and decision latency
- Risk register quality, triggers, and mitigation ownership
- Budget alignment to scope and forecast to complete

### Scope boundaries

- **Out of scope:** **estimation method** ownership (Fibonacci/t-shirt/**token bands**, roll-up math, **`ESTIMATES.md`** calibration) — **Estimation** Versona (`versona-estimation`); PM **consumes** sizes for commitments
- **Out of scope:** **product strategy**, roadmap **prioritization**, market/OKR **fit** (**Product Management** Versona)
- **Out of scope:** **requirements** depth / elicitation (**BA** Versona)
- **Out of scope:** **code quality** (Software Engineering Versona)
- **Out of scope:** **architecture** soundness (Architecture Versona)
- **Out of scope:** **testing strategy** detail (Testing Versona)
- **Out of scope:** **UX** craft (UX Versona)

